message.content: cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.PL, cs.SD, cs.ET - This paper investigates the impact of sleep deprivation on the performance of novice software developers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves analyzing the engagement and ability to apply a specific agile practice (test-first development), which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and programming languages (cs.PL). The study also involves analyzing the quality of the implementations, which relates to software design (cs.SD) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper suggests integrating the study of sleep with other psycho-physiological factors, which relates to emerging technologies (cs.ET).
